tasks.name: Ensure the Dryer is Empty: Prior to starting any wash cycles, check that the dryer is empty to allow immediate transfer of clothes after washing. This prevents any waiting period for the wet clothes, reducing the risk of them becoming moldy or smelly.

Treat Stains: Wet the stained articles and apply OxiClean spray. If time allows, soak the items to better treat tough stains.

Warm Darks (Underwear/Socks): Normal cycle with the manufacturer-recommended amount of detergent.
Cold Darks/Delicates: Wash on Delicates Cycle with the temperature set to Cold (ensure it's not Tap Cold to protect delicate fabrics).
Use 1 laundry pod for small/medium loads, and 2 for large loads.
Promptly transfer clothes from the washer to the dryer or designated hang drying area as soon as the wash cycle completes to prevent clothes from getting moldy or smelly.
Sort the washed clothes into those that need to be hang dried and those that can be dried by the dryer.

Hang Dry: Bras, women’s swimsuits, sports jerseys, leggings, tops with padding, women’s exercise clothing (e.g. tank tops, all LuluLemon), other delicates, expensive tops, blazers, sweaters, newer dry fit clothes, and any other delicate clothes or clothes prone to shrinking or damage.  When in doubt, check the garment tag for specific care instructions.
Tumble Dry: Jeans, pajamas, most men’s clothes, underwear, socks
Whites and Warm Darks: Normal cycle with Medium heat. Consider using a dryer sheet for added freshness and static reduction.
Cold Darks/Delicates: Use the Delicates cycle and select Time Dry for 60 minutes on Low heat.
After the initial drying cycle, optionally De-Wrinkle garments using the Steam Sanitary cycle for 30 minutes to smooth out wrinkles and refresh items.
Remove the clothes from the dryer
Hanging: Items requiring hang-drying should be promptly placed on hangers to minimize wrinkles and simplify storage.
Folding: Neatly fold dry laundry, sorting it by room or personal ownership to streamline the process of putting away.
